Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.48,0:01:38.00,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,It’s cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.44,0:01:42.51,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Oh that’s right…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.51,0:01:45.07,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I fell asleep yesterday after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.14,0:01:51.15,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo’s not here, so maybe I’ll \Ngo back to sleep in his bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.36,0:01:56.16,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,She’s gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.86,0:01:59.62,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.99,0:02:00.73,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.22,0:02:02.83,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Gone! Gone! Gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.83,0:02:04.46,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Gone! Gone! Gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.58,0:02:07.85,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Gone! Gone! Gone! Gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.85,0:02:09.19,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,She’s gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.24,0:02:13.90,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Where’d she go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.90,0:02:16.86,B2,WEATHERMAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The typical winter pressure \Nsystem will make way {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.86,0:02:19.92,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}for mostly sunny forecasts \Ntoday in the Pacific region.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.57,0:02:23.85,B2,WEATHERMAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Temperatures will be at \Naverage highs in most areas. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.85,0:02:25.58,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.58,0:02:29.00,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,What’re you doing up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.24,0:02:36.46,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,No one saw you, I hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.96,0:02:37.98,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Listen…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.73,0:02:41.93,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I brought you here without \Ntelling any of the people here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.93,0:02:44.30,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t take one step \Noutside this room, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.81,0:02:47.35,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Think what would happen \Nif they found out
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:48.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought a young girl here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.86,0:02:51.52,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,They’ll think I’m a \Npervert and kick me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.90,0:02:53.18,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,They’d do that to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.68,0:02:56.07,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is something wrong, Brother? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:01.70,B2,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,PERVERT
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.94,0:03:05.27,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,My name’s Kon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.71,0:03:07.24,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,You probably don’t remember
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.24,0:03:08.66,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,but I helped you yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.33,0:03:10.76,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,What’s your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.22,0:03:12.48,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:14.59,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,I won’t tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:22.21,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.21,0:03:23.59,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,I said I won’t tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.19,0:03:26.31,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Go away! Pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.86,0:03:29.63,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Who’re you calling a pervert?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.63,0:03:31.05,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t come near me, pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.58,0:03:32.69,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your hands off me, pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.96,0:03:46.26,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What’s the matter with everyone? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.96,0:03:49.03,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Were they brainwashed by someone? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.13,0:03:52.82,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, it didn’t seem that way. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.23,0:03:55.19,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo… Ichigo…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.87,0:04:01.91,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Rukia…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.63,0:04:06.72,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, would you like something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.95,0:04:10.89,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something you’d like?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.91,0:04:20.40,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Can’t you hear me, stupid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.68,0:04:30.12,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Oww…!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.76,0:04:31.68,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Where…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.40,0:04:34.00,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Where is this place, stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.00,0:04:35.68,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,What’s with the “stupid”?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.08,0:04:38.10,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,You’re at my place in Karakura Town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.46,0:04:40.60,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it’s sorta my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.01,0:04:42.31,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Karakura Town…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.66,0:04:45.18,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,So, where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.18,0:04:46.77,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do I need \Nto say to make it clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.13,0:04:48.98,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,You don’t need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.51,0:04:52.21,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you not only a pervert, \Nbut an idiot as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.54,0:04:53.85,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.13,0:04:56.81,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not stupid, or a pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.29,0:05:00.85,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I not only helped you, I even \Nlooked after you, yet…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.85,0:05:01.73,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Brother. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.76,0:05:05.49,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You’ve been making \Nway too much noise. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.86,0:05:07.51,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.17,0:05:09.36,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,I’m coming in…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.71,0:05:11.58,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,{\i0}Wait…Wait just a second! {\i1}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.43,0:05:14.54,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,What’s the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.77,0:05:16.69,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.69,0:05:18.54,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Doing my vocal exercises.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.69,0:05:22.52,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,I’m leaving for school.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.52,0:05:25.22,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,You’d better hurry too, \Nor you’ll be late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.45,0:05:27.15,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.07,0:05:36.27,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,She almost found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.25,0:05:38.13,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Perverted freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.93,0:05:41.15,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Perverted freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.31,0:05:43.28,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I didn’t…mean to…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.28,0:05:44.33,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Perverted freak!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.33,0:05:46.77,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I didn’t \Nmean to do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.36,0:05:50.32,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, I’m not interested \Nin little kids like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.65,0:05:52.91,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,If you’re not interested, \Nwhy’d you help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:56.57,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t recall asking for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.57,0:05:57.54,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid perverted freak!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.94,0:06:01.17,B2,KON (M),0000,0000,0000,,What an unlikable brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.00,0:06:12.20,B2,UKITAKE,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t imagine Ichigo \Ncould possibly be
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.20,0:06:14.01,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,involved in this incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.37,0:06:16.80,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.35,0:06:21.40,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,But then how do you \Nexplain that evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.71,0:06:25.96,B2,GENRYUSAI,0000,0000,0000,,What is the important item?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.85,0:06:29.20,B2,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,We found it near the area where we were
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:31.56,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,supposed to rendezvous with \NCaptain Kurotsuchi’s group.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:34.66,B2,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t know what connection \Nit might have to the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.94,0:06:36.93,B2,UKITAKE,0000,0000,0000,,This is…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.96,0:06:40.67,B2,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,But I believe it warrants \Ninvestigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.29,0:06:48.09,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,A Substitute Soul Reaper Combat Pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.85,0:06:51.54,B2,UKITAKE,0000,0000,0000,,That is definitely the one I gave him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.28,0:06:55.01,B2,UKITAKE,0000,0000,0000,,It’s unthinkable that anyone \Nother than Ichigo would have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.56,0:06:57.18,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,You’re right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.77,0:06:59.09,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,But I believe…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.79,0:07:01.77,B2,UKITAKE,0000,0000,0000,,What’s happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.13,0:07:04.37,B2,REAPER,0000,0000,0000,,Reporting!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.78,0:07:07.31,B2,REAPER,0000,0000,0000,,Substitute Soul Reaper Ichigo Kurosaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.31,0:07:09.25,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,who was detained as a material \Nwitness in the case
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.25,0:07:11.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,involving the disappearance of Soul \NReapers in the Precipice World,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.24,0:07:13.80,B2,REAPER,0000,0000,0000,,has disappeared from jail!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.07,0:07:19.12,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I have to run?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.43,0:07:21.33,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,We’re heading to Hakuto Gate
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.63,0:07:23.24,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,to get us out of the Seireitei!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.64,0:07:29.01,B2,ICHIGO (whisper),0000,0000,0000,,If I give them a good explanation, \Nthey’ll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.60,0:07:31.58,B2,ICHIGO (whisper),0000,0000,0000,,Is doing something like \Nthis a good idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.90,0:07:34.33,B2,RUKIA (whisper),0000,0000,0000,,It’s not…normally.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.06,0:07:37.51,B2,RUKIA (whisper),0000,0000,0000,,But don’t you think \Nsomething’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.78,0:07:40.52,B2,ICHIGO (whisper),0000,0000,0000,,What did I do, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.73,0:07:42.50,B2,RUKIA (whisper),0000,0000,0000,,I don’t know, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.34,0:07:44.91,B2,RUKIA (whisper),0000,0000,0000,,I did some checking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.18,0:07:48.21,B2,RUKIA (whisper),0000,0000,0000,,It appears a time gap \Nhas formed between
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.21,0:07:50.49,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,the Soul Society and the \NWorld of the Living.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.41,0:07:55.42,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Renji!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.42,0:07:56.27,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Ikkaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.27,0:07:57.42,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.41,0:08:00.16,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Ichigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.43,0:08:02.87,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,You’ll have to return \Nto jail quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.34,0:08:04.80,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You guys too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.18,0:08:09.72,B2,AKON,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.72,0:08:12.72,B2,AKON,0000,0000,0000,,Our person in charge of the Precipice \NWorld is out doing a survey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.72,0:08:14.43,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,That can’t be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.83,0:08:17.41,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,We’ve been in a constant \Nstate of emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.81,0:08:18.94,B2,AKON,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.23,0:08:21.63,B2,AKON,0000,0000,0000,,We did indeed record \NSpiritual Pressure in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.63,0:08:23.84,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,the Precipice World during the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.75,0:08:27.77,B2,AKON,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like me to compare it to \NIchigo Kurosaki’s Spiritual Pressure?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.31,0:08:30.01,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,No, that won’t be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.83,0:08:33.87,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve no doubt that the \NSpiritual Pressure was his.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.85,0:08:42.59,B2,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find out anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.45,0:08:47.75,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Captain Kuchiki. Thank \Nyou for all your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.18,0:08:51.17,B2,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you’re doing in the \Nmiddle of an emergency deployment?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.36,0:08:53.19,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.66,0:08:55.68,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,How about you, Captain Kuchiki?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.93,0:08:58.44,B2,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,They‘ll do fine without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.44,0:09:00.04,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,That’s nice to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.04,0:09:02.28,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me if I offended you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.80,0:09:05.64,B2,SHUNSUI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, guess I’ll go \Ndeploy my men too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.38,0:09:17.48,B2,UNOHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Isane.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.48,0:09:19.62,B2,ISANE,0000,0000,0000,,It’s this way, Captain Unohana.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.07,0:09:27.28,B2,UNOHANA,0000,0000,0000,,The Senkaimon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.72,0:09:29.33,B2,ISANE,0000,0000,0000,,When we came through,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.33,0:09:30.81,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,there was a slight variance \Nin the Spiritual Pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.81,0:09:31.59,B2,UNOHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.73,0:09:37.05,B2,ISANE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sensing something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.60,0:09:38.58,B2,UNOHANA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.36,0:09:42.37,B2,UNOHANA,0000,0000,0000,,I believe I need more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.21,0:09:44.40,B2,UNOHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.12,0:09:46.03,B2,ISANE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma’am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.20,0:09:49.19,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,We have no intention of killing you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.19,0:09:50.92,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,as long as you quietly \Nturn yourselves in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.92,0:09:53.76,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Though, I don’t think \Nthat’ll happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.63,0:09:56.48,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us one thing, Renji.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.14,0:09:59.03,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Why is Ichigo a suspect?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.61,0:10:00.99,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Your Combat Pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.10,0:10:03.35,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,My Combat Pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.35,0:10:04.20,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.75,0:10:07.71,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,It was presented as evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.72,0:10:10.16,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.78,0:10:17.05,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My Combat Pass! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.91,0:10:22.51,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I lost it when the Cleaner attacked \Nus in the Precipice World.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.82,0:10:24.43,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,We found that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.86,0:10:26.60,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,your Combat Pass was there
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.60,0:10:28.89,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,in the Precipice World several days ago
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:31.21,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,at about the very same time that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.21,0:10:33.44,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Kurotsuchi and \Nthe others disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.66,0:10:35.38,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean “several \Ndays ago”?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.71,0:10:37.58,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,We passed through the \NPrecipice World yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.58,0:10:39.23,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,shortly after noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.83,0:10:40.91,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,And are you accusing me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.91,0:10:42.96,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,of eliminating Captain \NKurotsuchi and the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.82,0:10:45.45,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m no magician, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.45,0:10:46.66,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Ichigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.66,0:10:48.04,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,I’m beginning to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.04,0:10:48.93,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Understand what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.65,0:10:51.97,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,The question of why your Combat Pass
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.97,0:10:53.03,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,was presented as evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.03,0:10:55.39,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,even before we left the \NWorld of the Living
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.39,0:10:56.67,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,is definitely a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.28,0:10:59.93,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,But one thing is clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:03.72,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever is responsible \Nfor trying to frame you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.72,0:11:06.20,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,is the mastermind behind this incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.11,0:11:10.21,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,So you’re saying that guy \Nis manipulating everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.21,0:11:12.23,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t really understand \Nwhat’s going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.59,0:11:16.82,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,but we’re not doing \Nthis because we want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.82,0:11:21.93,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,But if your resistance \Nmeans we can fight again,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.93,0:11:24.14,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,that’s just fine with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.85,0:11:27.43,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,You haven’t lost your \NSpirit Energy yet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.43,0:11:30.21,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Before your Spirit Energy is gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.80,0:11:32.77,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s have one last fierce fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.33,0:11:35.34,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Extend, Hozukimaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.83,0:11:44.26,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Roar, Zabimaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.84,0:11:59.90,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Why’re you doing this, Renji?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.37,0:12:03.86,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really believe Ichigo \Ncould cause this incident?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.23,0:12:05.82,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.31,0:12:07.70,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Then why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.11,0:12:09.87,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t help myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.87,0:12:13.32,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not doing this because I want to!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.18,0:12:20.50,B2,RUKIA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When…did he become this powerful?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.11,0:12:23.29,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,If you’re going to stop us, \Nyou’ll have to fight us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.29,0:12:24.18,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Rukia!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.89,0:12:28.51,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Renji!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.00,0:12:31.10,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Ikkaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.10,0:12:32.98,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I have no reason to fight you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.48,0:12:35.94,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,The same goes for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.94,0:12:39.01,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,but I don’t need a reason \Nto fight a strong opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:40.79,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.17,0:12:42.44,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.19,0:12:46.95,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,If you don’t fight back, I can’t \Nguarantee you’ll keep your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.39,0:12:49.37,B2,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you’re the opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.78,0:12:53.62,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,He’s not bluffing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.93,0:12:56.08,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Renji! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.32,0:12:57.65,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.30,0:13:01.61,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys really under \Nsomeone’s control?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.18,0:13:04.45,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You leave me no choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.99,0:13:06.30,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Bankai!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.61,0:13:16.90,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,You’re finally going to fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.61,0:13:19.40,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.19,0:13:22.94,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Bakudo 73: Tozansho!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.94,0:13:23.61,B2,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.38,0:13:30.53,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Yoruichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.84,0:13:32.41,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo… Kuchiki…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.68,0:13:33.42,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.02,0:13:44.78,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You saved us, Yoruichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.16,0:13:47.24,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,We can’t stay here long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.52,0:13:48.27,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.62,0:13:51.10,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,But something’s wrong with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.39,0:13:52.85,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.85,0:13:56.02,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,The look in Renji’s eyes was \Ndead serious about killing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.33,0:13:58.44,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that can’t be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.89,0:14:02.57,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn’t the real Abarai \Nor the real Madarame.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.82,0:14:04.04,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.14,0:14:07.07,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.07,0:14:09.11,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Not real? What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.44,0:14:13.37,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Were you fighting without \Nhaving realized that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.38,0:14:17.33,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,But…their Spiritual Pressure was \Nthe same as it always was, and…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:18.88,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,He’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.88,0:14:21.79,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,But they seemed to be much \Nmore powerful than I recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.32,0:14:23.62,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.33,0:14:27.76,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they are very \Nwell made, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.24,0:14:29.42,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Well made?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.27,0:14:33.70,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Soul Reapers require a \Nvessel for their Konpaku
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.70,0:14:35.97,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to function in \Nthe World of the Living.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.45,0:14:38.06,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, a gigai.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.13,0:14:41.15,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time, bodies that serve as
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.15,0:14:44.08,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,vessels for a Konpaku exist \Nin the Soul Society, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.58,0:14:48.30,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the Soul Society \Nversions of a gigai, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.30,0:14:50.53,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that easier to understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.90,0:14:59.12,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,A Reigai.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.14,0:15:06.11,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,REIGAI
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.18,0:15:00.64,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Rei…gai?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.58,0:15:04.11,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,The Abarai and Madarame you saw earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.11,0:15:08.61,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,are fakes created by placing \Na near-perfect Konpaku
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.61,0:15:10.09,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,inside near-perfect Reigai.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.36,0:15:12.51,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Although fakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.16,0:15:16.10,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they’ve been created so that their \Nmemories, personalities, and thoughts,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.55,0:15:20.60,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}nearly everything, are almost \Nperfect copies of the real thing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.43,0:15:23.44,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What’s more, I have absolutely \Nno idea how many Reigai {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.44,0:15:27.97,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}have currently infiltrated the \NThirteen Court Guard Squads.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.71,0:15:30.35,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,But, I don’t get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.79,0:15:34.38,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn’t those so-called Reigai \Nbe unnecessary in the Soul Society,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.38,0:15:36.98,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,where the Konpaku itself \Nbecomes the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.48,0:15:39.89,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,That’s probably true for \Nordinary Soul Reapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.38,0:15:42.54,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,However, there are those for \Nwhom they are a necessity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.81,0:15:43.76,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,And they are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.69,0:15:49.10,B2,YORUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Reigai are indispensable for \Ndevelopment of, and experiments on,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:52.61,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,the Soul Candies in the Soul Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.09,0:15:54.84,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Then…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.31,0:15:57.32,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,The Department of Research \Nand Development…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.86,0:16:02.74,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,It’s probably certain that someone \Nin Squad 12 is secretly involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.24,0:16:06.00,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.00,0:16:08.26,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo! Where did he go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.55,0:16:09.98,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Probably to Squad 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.51,0:16:12.76,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll do something to \Nthrow off security.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.17,0:16:16.47,B2,YORUICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Rukia, you rendezvous with \NIchigo to gather information.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.86,0:16:22.54,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.82,0:16:24.04,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.35,0:16:26.00,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m storming into Squad 12!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:27.18,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.49,0:16:30.49,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,You’re not going to \Nsucceed by storming into
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.49,0:16:32.14,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,the main compound without a plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.77,0:16:35.00,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,We’ll secretly sneak into Squad 12
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.00,0:16:37.15,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and gather as much \Ninformation as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.70,0:16:38.80,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.22,0:16:40.11,B2,REAPER A,0000,0000,0000,,North!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.65,0:16:42.60,B2,REAPER A,0000,0000,0000,,They’re headed for Kokuryo Gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.54,0:16:48.50,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,Department of Research and Development
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.76,0:16:51.15,B2,REAPER A,0000,0000,0000,,Sure is boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:53.80,B2,REAPER B,0000,0000,0000,,At least it’s better than getting \Nsome weird additional assignment!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.76,0:17:02.75,B2,AKON,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.99,0:17:04.58,B2,AKON,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.48,0:17:08.82,B2,AKON,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.30,0:17:24.49,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.49,0:17:27.31,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to secretly sneaking in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.69,0:17:30.21,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Is it okay to use such \Nan obvious Bakudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.21,0:17:32.44,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,This is no time to debate that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.97,0:17:41.81,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,So what now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.81,0:17:44.45,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Checking the records of past movement \Nthrough the Precipice World.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.84,0:17:48.05,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,There should be someone in here that \Nholds a clue to what’s happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.50,0:17:54.72,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.02,0:17:55.99,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.99,0:17:57.93,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Can you go back a few windows?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.76,0:18:00.53,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.62,0:18:05.07,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,So it’s that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.90,0:18:13.12,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Gone missing in the \NWorld of the Living;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.12,0:18:15.00,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,later found in Karakura Town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.56,0:18:19.06,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,If she refuses capture, elimination…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.51,0:18:21.82,B2,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,is authorized?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.14,0:18:27.40,B2,YUZU,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will you get that, Brother? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.97,0:18:29.24,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Okay. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.17,0:18:37.17,B2,KIRA/NANAO,0000,0000,0000,,You…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.64,0:18:40.01,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you people?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.25,0:18:43.46,B2,KAGEROZA,0000,0000,0000,,You are Ichigo Kurosaki’s \NSoul Candy, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.46,0:18:45.27,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,You’re very well-informed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.27,0:18:47.20,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Aren’t you…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.81,0:18:49.53,B2,NANAO,0000,0000,0000,,We are from the Seireitei.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.13,0:18:53.78,B2,KIRA,0000,0000,0000,,We understand that a Soul Reaper \Nnamed Nozomi Kujo is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.78,0:18:54.98,B2,KIRA,0000,0000,0000,,We’ve come to take her with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.98,0:18:56.59,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Nozomi Kujo?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.07,0:18:58.34,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Take her with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.91,0:19:01.09,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you mean that kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.09,0:19:02.95,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,You mean she’s a Soul Reaper?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.32,0:19:05.33,B2,KAGEROZA,0000,0000,0000,,Hadn’t you heard from either
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.33,0:19:08.41,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Substitute Soul Reaper Ichigo \NKurosaki or Rukia Kuchiki?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.76,0:19:11.38,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,N-No…I hadn’t heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.60,0:19:13.41,B2,NANAO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.41,0:19:15.34,B2,NANAO,0000,0000,0000,,We were under the \Nimpression that you had.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.60,0:19:16.87,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.87,0:19:19.59,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll gift-wrap her and give her to \Nyou if you’ll take her with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.46,0:19:22.50,B2,KAGEROZA,0000,0000,0000,,So…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.57,0:19:25.59,B2,KAGEROZA,0000,0000,0000,,Where is she now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.61,0:19:28.98,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Up…stairs…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.98,0:19:30.81,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll bring her down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.99,0:19:32.79,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,It’ll be a relief!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.79,0:19:34.32,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.15,0:19:43.20,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.54,0:19:45.98,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,There’re some people here from \Nthe Soul Society to pick you up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.32,0:19:48.75,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,What’re you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.26,0:19:53.08,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.58,0:19:54.57,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.57,0:19:55.53,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.71,0:19:57.63,B2,KIRA,0000,0000,0000,,She’s making a run for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.79,0:20:01.97,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.13,0:20:03.51,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Bad! Bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.51,0:20:05.57,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Bad! Bad! Bad! Bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.31,0:20:07.91,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Bad! Bad! Bad! Bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.91,0:20:09.06,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Bad! Bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.23,0:20:18.01,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,What’s with those guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.54,0:20:20.99,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,This is really bad, isn’t it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.88,0:20:24.41,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hado 58:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.94,0:20:25.90,B2,NOZOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Tenran!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.12,0:20:30.00,B2,KIRA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.45,0:20:58.06,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you all right?
